Many of you helped, and well, I can't really explain what GP is to non-gamers, so I've come here to brag a bit on how GuildPortal is doing.. ;)<br>
<br>
Today, we're standing at 366 hosted guilds across three different games (EQ, AO, DAOC), and finally, 3001 users!  I didn't expect to break the 3k user mark until the first month of next year, and am very happy with the fact that over 80% of the new users we get are navigating directly to www.guildportal.com instead of being referred by another site.  That suggests word of mouth, and that means word must be pretty good!<br>
<br>
Did I mention that the CEO of ezBoard entered into negotiations with me for about a week, and at the end of that week, I turned him down?  EGO BOOST!  Hehe..  He wanted GP to use ezBoard as our forum hosting provider, stating that GP wouldn't be able to manage the growth and that message forums would account for 80% of our bandwidth.. Well, they account for roughly 20% of our bandwidth, as people spend an awful lot of time using the other features that ezBoard doesn't provide (probably why they're our 3rd biggest referrer -- people posting links to GP on their ezBoards).  He started being a jackass, so I told him, "Look, the day you start taking customers from MY site, we'll talk, but at this point your people are coming to me."  Booyah!  Burned a bridge!  lol<br>
<br>
OK, so I'm spastic.  The current feature sets I'm working on are : quest tracking, guild banking, cutom tab images, and guild alliances (shared forums, events, voting polls).<br>
<br>
Thanks again for your input (past and current) on how to make a great product for this little niche in the gaming industry.  One day I plan to offer external services to gaming publishers so that they can tie their systems into ours and manage their offline communities via XML web services using our base portal engine.<br>
